						<summary>

						<p>c. 9th Century.</p>						

						<p>Gift of 50 sheep by Chāttaṅgāri, for a lamp to the temple of Tirukkāṭṭām-paḷḷi-dēva at Kuṟaṇḍi in Veṇbu-nāḍu. The ūrār and <hi rend="italic">gaṇattār</hi> undertook to protect the gift.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi>, Vol. XIV, No. 34.]</p>						

